========================================================================
@node concept "What is Scatterbrain for, anyway?"

Do you have lots of ideas, but no time to develop them?  Or do you have
so much to do that little things are always falling through the cracks?
Or do you just have a poor memory?  Then maybe Scatterbrain is for you.

I wrote Scatterbrain because, to some extent, I fit all those descriptions.
Scatterbrain itself is one of those ideas that I had, but never had time
to develop.  Until now.

Here's how it works: enter your idea via the @{" input gadget " LINK "Input Gadget"}.  If you
prefix it with a @{" label " LINK "Synonym"}, you can then break down your idea into smaller
and smaller, manageable steps (also entered via the input gadget.)
Do this for every idea you have whenever you're near your computer --
to make it easier, Scatterbrain's input gadget can be quickly activated 
by a @{" hotkey " LINK "Hotkey"}.

Once you have a database of ideas, you can generate a list of things
to do.  Go to the @{" checklist window " LINK "Checklist Window"}, and select @{" Generate " LINK "Checklist-Generate Menu Item"} from the
@{" checklist menu " LINK "Checklist Menu"}.  Now you can check things off as you get them done.
After you've done a few, select @{" Reconcile " LINK "Checklist-Reconcile Menu Item"} from the menu.  If you run
of things to do, select @{" Generate " LINK "Checklist-Generate Menu Item"} again to see if there's more stuff
for you to get done.

See also @{" Tips on using Scatterbrain " LINK tips}.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node tips "Tips on using Scatterbrain"

1. Organize your projects into categories, and enter the projects as
   sub-projects of those categories.  This way, you can hide the
   contents of entire categories easily.

2. Use short but easy to remember labels, so that you can enter steps
   or sub-projects which fumbling around looking for the proper label.

3. If you get confused and use a label that doesn't exist, enter that
   label as a synonym for the label you meant to use.  That way, the 
   next time you get mixed up, it will still work.

@endnode
========================================================================
@node Glossary

Here are some terms that I use a lot in this document.  Click on the
word or phrase to see what is meant by it.

    @{" Extension           " LINK Extension   }
    @{" Hotkey              " LINK Hotkey      }
    @{" Label               " LINK Synonyms    }
    @{" MUI escape sequence " LINK MUIEsc      }
    @{" Project             " LINK Project     }
    @{" Step                " LINK Step        }
    @{" Sub-project         " LINK Sub-project }
    @{" Synonym             " LINK Synonym     }
    @{" Tooltypes           " LINK Tooltypes   }

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node Extension

The last part of a filename, following a dot.  For example, the extension
of "SB.SB" is "SB", and the extension of "SB.bak" is "bak".  The filename 
"Checklist" does not have an extension.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node Hotkey 

The hotkey is a keystroke which you can specify, which causes the 
@{" Input Window " LINK "Input Window"} to open if it was closed, and come to the front.  It also
causes the @{" Input Gadget " LINK "Input Gadget"} to activate, so that you may enter data.

The hotkey may be configured by the @{" Hotkey String Gadget " LINK "Hotkey String Gadget"} on the 
@{" Commodity Page " LINK "Preferences Commodity Page"} of the @{" Preferences Window " LINK "Preferences Window"}.

If a CX_POPKEY @{" tooltype " LINK Tooltypes} is specified in the Scatterbrain icon, and
Scatterbrain is started from the Workbench, it will take precedence
over the setting in the @{" Commodity Page " LINK "Preferences Commodity Page"}.  CX_POPKEY may also be
specified as a command line argument if Scatterbrain is started from
the Shell.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node MUIEsc "MUI Escape Sequence"

The MUI escape sequences for specifying an image are fully described 
in the MUI developers documentation.  However, I will give some brief
information here for convenience.

The sequences are all of the form "\33I[s]".  Do not enter the quotes
into the string gadget, and do not enter the 's', but replace it with
one of the following (again, do not enter the quotes):

    "3:x" -- where 'x' is replaced with the name of a BOOPSI image class

    "4:x" -- where 'x' is replaced with the name of a brush

    "5:x" -- where 'x' is replaced with the name of a graphics file
             which can be loaded by the datatypes on your system.
	     (Requires AmigaDOS 3.0 or later.)

    "6:x" -- where 'x' is replaced by a @{" number " LINK "Image Numbers"} which specifies
             a standard MUI image.

Some examples:

    "\33I[5:SYS:Pictures/Marble.iff]" would specify the IFF picture
    Marble.iff in directory SYS:Pictures.

    "\33I[6:15]" would specify the MUI CheckMark image.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Image Numbers"

 0     Window background
 1     Requester background
 2     Button background
 3     List background
 4     Text background
 5     Prop gadget background
 7     Selected gadget background
 8     Listview cursor background
 9     Listview selected background
10     Listview cursor & selected background
11     Up arrow
12     Down arrow
13     Left arrow
14     Right arrow
15     Checkmark image
16     RadioButton image
17     Cycle gadget image
18     PopUp image
19     PopFile image
20     PopDrawer image
21     Prop knob image
22     Drawer image
23     HardDisk image
24     Disk image
25     Chip image
26     Volume image
27     PopUp background
28     Network image
29     Assign image
30     Tape play image
31     Tape playback image
32     Tape pause image
33     Tape stop image
34     Tape record image
35     Group background
36     Slider background
37     Slider knob image
38     Tape up image
39     Tape down image

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node Project

A project is an entry in the @{" projects listview " LINK "Project Listview"}.  Projects are 
organized in a hierarchy, so each project may have one or more
@{" sub-projects " LINK "Sub-project"} and/or @{" steps " LINK "Step"} beneath it.  "Project", "sub-project",
and "step" are all basically the same thing -- the different names
just denote their place within the hierarchy of projects.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node Step

A step is an entry in the @{" projects listview " LINK "Project Listview"} which does not have any
steps or @{" sub-projects " LINK "Sub-project"} which belong to it.

A project's steps and @{" sub-projects " LINK "Sub-project"} are displayed beneath it and
indented, provided that they have not been hidden via the @{" Hide " LINK "Project Hide Button"} button,
or similar means.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node Sub-project

A sub-project is an entry in the project window which has one or more
@{" steps " LINK "Step"} or sub-projects which belong to it.

A project's @{" steps " LINK "Step"} and sub-projects are displayed beneath it and
indented, provided that they have not been hidden via the @{" Hide " LINK "Project Hide Button"} button,
or similar means.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node Synonym "Labels, or Synonyms"

Labels and synonyms (the two terms can be used interchangeably) are
short names which point to @{" projects " LINK "Project"}.  They are a useful way to very
quickly add a step to the hierarchy of projects.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node Tooltypes

Scatterbrain supports the following tooltypes if started from the
Workbench.  They may also be specified as command line arguments if
Scatterbrain is started from the Shell.  The values, if supplied,
override values in the @{" Preferences Window " LINK "Preferences Window"}.

    CX_POPKEY    Specifies the @{" hotkey " LINK "Hotkey"} to use.

    CX_POPUP     Specifies whether the @{" Input Window " LINK "Input Window"} should open when
                 you start Scatterbrain.  May be TRUE, YES, or ON for
                 a false value, or FALSE, NO, or OFF for a true value.

    CX_POPUPALL  Specifies whether the @{" Queue Window " LINK "Queue Window"}, @{" Projects Window " LINK "Projects Window"},
                 @{" Synonym Window " LINK "Synonym Window"}, and @{" Checklist Window " LINK "Checklist Window"} should open
                 when you start Scatterbrain, as well as the input 
                 window.  If CX_POPUP is false, this value is ignored.

    APPICON      Specifies the icon imagery to use when Scatterbrain
                 is iconified.  Do not supply the ".info" extension.
                 Use MUI Prefs to set the location of the icon, or
                 if you want Scatterbrain to start up iconified.

@endnode
========================================================================
@node ARexx

Here are the ARexx commands currently available:

    Standard MUI application ARexx commands:

        ACTIVATE      
        DEACTIVATE
        SHOW              For more information on any of 
        HIDE              these, see the MUI documentation.
        INFO ITEM/A
        HELP FILE/A
        QUIT FORCE/S

    ARexx commands specific to Scatterbrain:

        FLUSH      Same as the @{" Flush " LINK "Projects-Flush Menu Item"} item on the @{" Projects Menu " LINK "Projects Menu"}
        EXPIRE     Same as the @{" Expire " LINK "Projects-Expire Menu Item"} item on the @{" Projects Menu " LINK "Projects Menu"}
        SAVE       Same as the @{" Save " LINK "Project-Save Menu Item"} item on the @{" Project Menu " LINK "Project Menu"}
        REVERT     Same as the @{" Revert " LINK "Project-Revert Menu Item"} item on the @{" Project Menu " LINK "Projects Menu"}

@endnode
========================================================================
@node future "To Do ..."

Features I want to add, in no particular order:

+ Add localization for different languages.
+ Make Show & Hide work with multiselect.
+ Automatic expiration of old projects.
+ "Do In Any Order" projects should let you dynamically choose 
  which step to use in the checklist.
+ ARexx commands for every function of Scatterbrain.
+ Some way to set display, due, & expire dates from the input gadget,
  and in imported text files.
+ "Repeating projects" which automatically set a new display date
  for themselves and return to the "Ready" state whenever they're
  marked as "Done".
+ Remove the need to "Reconcile" the checklist
+ An easier way to "unpostpone" an item.  (Currently, you have to
  clear the "Display Date" field in the Project Info window.)

@endnode
========================================================================
@remark The rest of this file is primarily for use as on-line help text.
========================================================================
@node windows "List of Windows"
  
    @{u}List of Windows@{uu}

    @{" Input        " LINK "Input Window"       }    Where most new data is entered
    @{" Queue        " LINK "Queue Window"       }    Things Scatterbrain doesn't know how to file
    @{" Projects     " LINK "Project Window"     }    A hierarchical list of projects
    @{" Synonyms     " LINK "Synonym Window"     }    Abbreviations for projects
    @{" Project Info " LINK "Project Info Window"}    Details of a specific project
    @{" Checklist    " LINK "Checklist Window"   }    Project steps for you to work on now
    @{" Preferences  " LINK "Preferences Window" }    Customize how Scatterbrain works

    @{" About        " LINK "About Window"       }    Tells about this version of Scatterbrain
    @{" Gauges       " LINK "Gauge Window"       }    Contains I/O progress indicators

@endnode
========================================================================
@node "Input Window"

The input window contains one or two gadgets.  The @{" input gadget " LINK "Input Gadget"}, which
is always present, and the @{" change indicator " LINK "Change Indicator"}, which may be toggled on
or off from the @{" Indicators Page " LINK "Preferences Indicators Page"} of the @{" preferences window " LINK "Preferences Window"}. 

This is the window that pops up when you press the @{" hotkey " LINK "Hotkey"}.  Both the
hotkey and the screen on which the window is to pop up are configurable
from the @{" preferences window " LINK "Preferences Window"}, too.   The screen in configured on
the @{" Input Page " LINK "Preferences Input Page"} and the hotkey is configured on the @{" Commodity Page " LINK "Preferences Commodity Page"}.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------  
@node "Input Gadget"

This string gadget is the point at which new ideas are entered into the
database.

An idea may be entered by itself, in which case it will be filed away in
the @{" queue list " LINK "Queue Listview"}.

Or, it may be preceded by a label and a colon (':').  If the label exists
in the @{" synonym list " LINK "Synonym Listview"}, the idea will be filed under the corresponding
project in the @{" project list " LINK "Project Listview"}, minus the label and colon.

Either of the above two forms may be preceded by a label and a colon/equals 
pair (":=").  If the idea can be filed in the @{" project list " LINK "Project Listview"}, and the
label doesn't exist in the @{" synonym list " LINK "Synonym Listview"}, the label will be entered into
the @{" synonym list " LINK "Synonym Listview"}, and the idea filed in the @{" project list " LINK "Project Listview"}.  Otherwise,
it ends up in the @{" queue list " LINK "Queue Listview"}.

Also, a synonym for a synonym may be entered by using an equals sign ('=')
between the two synonyms.  Exactly one of the synonyms must already exist,
and no other data may be present in the input string.

Since the colon and equals sign are used to parse the input string,
they cannot be entered directly into an idea description.  I intend
to fix this somehow in a future release.  If you must have a colon
or equals sign in a project idea, you can edit the idea after it
has been filed in the @{" project list " LINK "Project Listview"}.

@{" See examples " LINK "Input Examples"}

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Input Examples"

In the following, @{b}bold@{ub} text indicates what would be entered.

1. @{b}:foo := text@{ub}  The colon with nothing preceding it means this 
   creates a project at the top level.  The project is described by 
   "text", and a label "foo" points to it.  Prefixing later input with 
   the label "foo:" would cause that input to be filed as a sub-project
   to this project.

2. @{b}foo: more text@{ub}  This adds a step to the project pointed to by
   the label "foo".  The step is described by "more text".

3. @{b}foo:bar:=even more text@{ub}  This adds a step to the project pointed
   to by the label "foo".  This step is described by "even more text",
   and has a label named "bar" which points to it.  This item could also
   have been entered as @{b}bar:=foo:even more text@{ub} -- so long as the
   ":" and ":=" are placed properly, order doesn't matter.  The ":" must
   follow the label which indicate which project this step will be a 
   child of.  The ":=" must follow the label which will be used to 
   indicate the project described by the text which follows.

4. @{b}foo=bar@{ub}  If you have entered the previosu three lines, this is 
   illegal, because both labels already exist.  The line will appear in 
   the @{" Queue Listview " LINK "Queue Listview"} so that you may edit it later, if you wish.  
   If your edits change it into a legal input, it will be filed properly
   elsewhere and removed from the queue listview.

5. @{b}baz=bar@{ub}  This creates a label "baz" which points to the same 
   project as "bar" does.  Order doesn't matter: this could also have 
   been entered as @{b}bar=baz@{ub}.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Change Indicator"

The change indicator shows you if any changes have been made since the
last load or save operation.  If you do not save these changes before
loading another file or quitting, they will be lost.

The presence or absence of the change indicator can configured via the
@{" indicator page " LINK "Preferences Indicators Page"} of the @{" preferences window " LINK "Preferences Window"}.  The text or images used to 
indicate "changed" or "not changed" can also be configured on that page.

@endnode
========================================================================
@node "Queue Window"

      @{u}Gadgets@{uu}

    @{" listview " LINK "Queue Listview"      }
    @{" string   " LINK "Queue String Gadget" }

     @{u}Buttons@{uu}

    @{" Del    " LINK "Del Button"          }
    @{" Un     " LINK "Un Button"           }
    @{" File   " LINK "Queue File Button"   }
    @{" Sort   " LINK "Queue Sort Button"   }
    @{" arrows " LINK "Queue Arrow Buttons" }

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Queue Listview"

The queue listview contains a list of all lines of input which could not
otherwise be processed or filed.

If later the database has changed in such a way that these items could
now be filed, click the @{" File button " LINK "Queue File Button"}, and they will be dealt with
appropriately.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Queue String Gadget"

This gadget allows you edit the currently active item from the 
@{" queue listview " LINK "Queue Listview"}.  Upon hitting the return key, Scatterbrain will
attempt to file the item again, in case you made changes which will
enable that.  For instance, you may have corrected a misspelled @{" label " LINK "Synonym"},
allowing Scatterbrain to figure out under which @{" project " LINK "Project"} this item 
should be filed.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Del Button" "Delete Button"

Clicking this button deletes all selected items in the corresponding
listview.  In some cases, it may not be possible to delete an item,
because it is in use (e.g. a synonym which is referenced by other
synonyms.)  In this case, first delete the items which are using this 
item.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Un Button" "Unselect All Button"

Clicking this button unselects all selected items in the corresponding
listview.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Queue File Button"

This button causes Scatterbrain to try again to file all items in the
@{" queue listview " LINK "Queue Listview"}.  This is useful, for instance, if you entered several
items with a non-existant label, and entered the label as a synonym
later.  After entering the label, you would click the File button, and
the items labeled would be filed under the corresponding project.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Queue Sort Button"

Clicking this button causes the contents of the @{" queue listview " LINK "Queue Listview"} to be
sorted in alphabetical order.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Queue Arrow Buttons"

The up and down arrows in the @{" Queue Window " LINK "Queue Window"} may be used to move the
active item up or down, respectively, in the @{" Queue Listview " LINK "Queue Listview"}.  These
buttons are always disabled when the @{" Queue Listview " LINK "Queue Listview"} is configured
to automatically sort its input.

The keyboard shortcut for these buttons are "u" for "Up" and "d" for
"Down", respectively.

@endnode
========================================================================
@node "Project Window"

      @{u}Gadgets@{uu}

    @{" listview " LINK "Project Listview"}
    @{" string   " LINK "Project String Gadget"}

    @{u}Buttons@{uu}

    @{" Del  " LINK "Del Button"}
    @{" Un   " LINK "Un Button"}
    @{" Show " LINK "Project Show Button"}
    @{" Hide " LINK "Project Hide Button"}
    @{" Grab " LINK "Project Grab Button"}
    @{" Add  " LINK "Project Add Button"}
 
      Arrow
     @{u}buttons@{uu}

    @{" up    " LINK "Project Up & Down Arrows"}
    @{" down  " LINK "Project Up & Down Arrows"}
    @{" left  " LINK "Project Left Arrow"}
    @{" right " LINK "Project Right Arrow"}

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Project Listview"

The project listview contains a hierarchical list of all projects that
Scatterbrain knows about.  The left column contains an indicator of
whether or not the project on that line has subprojects which are
currently hidden.  The right column contains a description of the
project, which may be indented to indicate how many levels down in the
hierarchy it is. 

The "hidden" and "shown" indicators may be configured on the @{" Projects Page " LINK "Preferences Projects Page"} 
of the @{" Preferences Window " LINK "Preferences Window"}.  Doubleclicking on either indicator will
change the state from "hidden" to "shown" or vice versa, and reveal or
hide, respectively, the project's subprojects.

Double-clicking on the project will cause the @{" Project Info Window " LINK "Project Info Window"} to
appear, and the gadgets in that window will be updated with the values
corresponding to the double-clicked project.

The text or image used for each level of indentation may be configured
via the @{" indent with " LINK "Indent With Gadget"} gadget, also on the project page of the preferences
window.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Project String Gadget"

This gadget allows you to edit the description of the project currently
under the listview cursor in the @{" Projects Listview " LINK "Project Listview"}.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Project Show Button"

Causes the active project in the @{" Projects Listview " LINK "Project Listview"} to reveal its
sub-projects, if they were hidden.

In @{" future versions " LINK future}, this will affect all currently selected projects,
not just the active project.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Project Hide Button"

Causes the active project in the @{" Projects Listview " LINK "Project Listview"} to hide its
sub-projects, if they were visible.

In @{" future versions " LINK future}, this will affect all currently selected projects,
not just the active project.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Project Grab Button"

This button causes a line to be grabbed from the @{" Queue Listview " LINK "Queue Listview"} and
inserted as a subproject of the project currently under the listview
cursor in the @{" Projects Listview " LINK "Project Listview"}.  Which line will be grabbed is
determined by the setting of the @{" grab from " LINK "Grab From Queue Gadget"} gadget on the @{" Queue Page " LINK "Preferences Queue Page"}
of the @{" Preferences Window " LINK "Preferences Window"}.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Project Add Button"

This button causes a new step to be added the currently active project.
This step will become active, so that the @{" string gadget " LINK "Project String Gadget"} may be used
to enter text for it.  To move the listview cursor back to where it
was before, use the right arrow key on the keyboard.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Project Up & Down Arrows"

These buttons move the active step up or down within the list of steps
of which it is a member.  

The keyboard shortcuts are "u" for "Up" and "d" for "Down", respectively.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Project Left Arrow"

This button moves all the currently selected project steps up one level.
Projects which aren't indented at all are not affected.

The keyboard shortcut for this button is "l" for "Left".

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Project Right Arrow"

This button moves the currently selected projects steps so that they
are now substeps of whichever project is active in the projects listview.

If only one step or sub-project is selected, then it becomes a child
of the project which precedes it in the listview at the same level
of indentation.

The keyboard shortcut for this button is "r" for "Right".

@endnode
========================================================================
@node "Synonym Window"

      @{u}Gadgets@{uu}

    @{" listview " LINK "Synonym Listview"}
    @{" strings  " LINK "Synonym String Gadgets"}

     @{u}Buttons@{uu}

    @{" Find " LINK "Synonym Find Button"}
    @{" Del  " LINK "Del Button"}
    @{" Un   " LINK "Un Button"}

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Synonym Listview"

This is the list of synonyms in the database.  A synonym in the left
column either stands for another synonym, or a project.  The right
column will contain either the name of another synonym, or "<PROJECT>",
respectively.

Double-clicking on an item in the list will make the list cursor jump
to the corresponding synonym or project.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Synonym String Gadgets"

These gadgets allow you to change synonym definitions.  

The left string allows you to change the name of the synonym.  You can
change it to anything which is not already a synonym, and which doesn't
contain a ':' or a '='.  If there are other synonym names which "point"
at this one, their right-column text will change automatically.

The right string changes the synonym to which this synonym name points.
You can change it to anything which is already a synonym.  If the
right-column text is "<PROJECT>", this gadget will be disabled.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Synonym Find Button"

This button causes the item in the @{" Projects Listview " LINK "Project Listview"} which corresponds
to the currently active synonym to be highlighted.  This behavior may
be modified according to the setting of the @{" Find Hidden Projects " LINK "Find Hidden Projects Gadget"} gadget
on the Behaviors Page of the @{" Projects Page " LINK "Preferences Projects Page"} of the @{" Preferences " LINK "Preferences Window"}
Window.

It may also cause the @{" Projects Window " LINK "Projects Window"} to open, come to the front and 
become the active window, depending on the setting of the 
@{" Find Activates Project Window " LINK FindActivate}, on the same page of the @{" Preferences " LINK "Preferences Window"}
Window.

Furthermore, the active synonym will be changed to the one directly
related to the higlighted project (i.e. <PROJECT> will be in the
second column of the listview.)

@endnode
========================================================================
@node "Project Info Window"

      @{u}Gadgets@{uu}

    @{" Do        " LINK "PInfo Do"}
    @{" State     " LINK "PInfo State"}
    @{" Synonym   " LINK "PInfo Synonym"}
    @{" Display   " LINK "PInfo Display"}
    @{" Do before " LINK "PInfo Do before"}
    @{" Expire    " LINK "PInfo Expire"}

    @{" Use       " LINK "PInfo Use"}
    @{" Cancel    " LINK "PInfo Cancel"}

    @{u}Other info@{uu}

    @{" Created  " LINK "PInfo Created"}
    @{" Changed  " LINK "PInfo Changed"}
    @{" Acted on " LINK "PInfo Acted on"}
    @{" text     " LINK "PInfo text"}

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "PInfo Do" "Project Info `Do' Cycle Gadget"

Determines the order in which the @{b}subitem@{ub} of this item are to be selected 
for the checklist by the @{" Generate " LINK "Checklist-Generate Menu Item} item of the @{" Checklist menu " LINK "Checklist Menu"}.

There are five choices:

    Do in sequence  -- Selects the first item which isn't Done or Expired.
    Do in any order -- for now, does the same as "Do in sequence".
    Do all at once  -- Selects all items which aren't Done or Expired.
    Do just one of  -- Selects this item, instead of one of its children.
    Do not generate -- No item is selected.

You must click on @{" Use " LINK "PInfo Use"} for any change to take effect.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "PInfo State" "Project Info `State' Cycle Gadget"

This gadget sets the current state of the project.

There are three choices:

    Ready    -- This project may be selected by the @{" checklist generator " LINK "Checklist-Generate Menu Item" 3}.
                This is the default.

    Done     -- This project has been completed.  Selecting @{" Flush " LINK "Projects-Flush Menu Item"} from 
                the @{" Projects Menu " LINK "Projects Menu"} will cause it to be deleted.

    Expired  -- The project was not completed before the date entered
                in the @{" Expire gadget " LINK "Pinfo Expire"}.  Selecting @{" Flush " LINK "Projects-Flush Menu Item"} from the 
                @{" Projects Menu " LINK "Projects Menu"} will cause it to be deleted.

You must click on @{" Use " LINK "PInfo Use"} for any change to take effect.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "PInfo Synonym" "Project Info `Synonym' String Gadget"

This gadget allows you to add a @{" label " LINK "Synonym"} to a project or step which
doesn't have one, or to change or delete one which already exists.
You may use any string which is not already being used as a synonym
for a different project or step, and which does not contain a ':' or
a '='.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "PInfo Display" "Project Info `Display' Date Gadget"

Project steps will not appear in the @{" checklist " LINK "Checklist Listview"} until after this
date.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "PInfo Do before" "Project Info `Do before' Date Gadget"

This gadget allows you to enter a "due date" for the current project.
You may choose to sort the @{" checklist " LINK "Checklist Listview"} based on this date.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "PInfo Expire" "Project Info `Expire' Date Gadget"

After this date, the project's @{" state " LINK "PInfo State"} should change to "Expired".
Currently, you must periodically select the @{" Expire item " LINK "Projects-Expire Menu Item"} from the
@{" Projects Menu " LINK "Projects Menu"} in order for this to occurs.  In a @{" future version " LINK future},
it will happen automatically at the appointed time.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "PInfo Use" "Project Info `Use' Gadget"

Causes any changes you have made to the current project info to take
effect on the corresponding project.  The "changed" date will be updated
to the current time.  Also, the "last action" date will be update to
the same time, if a transition was made from some other state to the
"Done" state.

Depending on the setting of the @{" Close Project Info " LINK "Close PInfo Gadget"} gadget on the
@{" Project Info Page " LINK "Preferences Project Info Page"} of the @{" Preferences Window " LINK "Preferences Window"}, the window may also
automatically close.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "PInfo Cancel" "Project Info `Cancel' Date Gadget"

Causes any changes you have made to the current project info to be lost.
The @{" Project Info Window " LINK "Project Info Window"} is cleared and the gadgets are disabled.

Depending on the setting of the @{" Close Project Info " LINK "Close PInfo Gadget"} gadget on the
@{" Project Info Page " LINK "Preferences Project Info Page"} of the @{" Preferences Window " LINK "Preferences Window"}, the window may also
automatically close.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "PInfo Created" "Project Info Creation Date Display"

Displays the date and time at which this item was entered.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "PInfo Changed" "Project Info Last Change Date Display"

Displays the date and time at which this item last had its
project info modified.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "PInfo Acted on" "Project Info Last Action Date Display"

Displays the date and time at which this project, or one of its
sub-projects, last made the transition from some other state to
the "Done" state.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "PInfo text" "Project Info Description"

This area displays the text which describes the project associated with
the data in the other gadgets in this window.  You cannot change the 
text here -- to do that, use the @{" Project window " LINK "Project Window"}'s @{" string gadget " LINK "Project String Gadget"}

@endnode
========================================================================
@node "Checklist Window"

      @{u}Gadget@{uu}

    @{" listview " LINK "Checklist Listview"}

     @{u}Buttons@{uu}

    @{" Done     " LINK "Checklist Done Button"     }
    @{" Postpone " LINK "Checklist Postpone Button" }
    @{" Find     " LINK "Checklist Find Button"     }
    @{" Un       " LINK "Unselect Button"           }

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Checklist Listview"

This listview provides a checklist of all the project steps that
are currently available for you to work on.  In the left column, 
a pseudo-gadget is provided for you to check things off as you do 
them.  When you have done a few, select @{" Reconcile " LINK "Checklist-Reconcile Menu Item"} from the
@{" Checklist Menu " LINK "Checklist Menu"} to delete the completed items from the checklist,
and record in the database that they are completed.  If you do not
reconcile before saving, your accomplishments will not be saved in
the database.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Checklist Done Button"

Check off the selected items from the @{" Checklist Listview " LINK "Checklist Listview"}.  When you
select @{" Reconcile " LINK "Checklist-Reconcile Menu Item"} from the @{" Checklist Menu " LINK "Checklist Menu"}, the items which have
been checked off will be marked as "Done" in the @{" Projects Listview " LINK "Project Listview"}.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Checklist Postpone Button"

Postpone the selected items from the @{" Checklist Listview " LINK "Checklist Listview"} until
tomorrow.  This is accomplished by setting the @{" display date " LINK "PInfo Display"} of the
affected projects to tomorrow at midnight.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Checklist Find Button"

This button causes the item in the @{" Projects Listview " LINK "Project Listview"} which corresponds
to the currently active checklist entry to be highlighted.  This behavior 
may be modified according to the setting of the @{" Find Hidden Projects " LINK "Find Hidden Project Gadget"}
gadget on the Behaviors Page of the @{" Projects Page " LINK "Preferences Projects Page"} of the @{" Preferences " LINK "Preferences Window"}
Window.

It may also cause the @{" Projects Window " LINK "Projects Window"} to open, come to the front and 
become the active window, depending on the setting of the 
@{" Find Activates Project Window " LINK FindActivate}, on the same page of the @{" Preferences " LINK "Preferences Window"}
Window..

These actions can also be caused by double-clicking on an item in the
@{" Checklist Listview " LINK "Checklist Listview"}.

@endnode
========================================================================
@node "Preferences Window"

     @{u}List of Pages@{uu}

    @{" Input         " LINK "Preferences Input Page"         }
    @{" Queue         " LINK "Preferences Queue Page"         }
    @{" Projects      " LINK "Preferences Projects Page"      }
    @{" Project info  " LINK "Preferences Project Info Page"  }
    @{" Checklist     " LINK "Preferences Checklist Page"     }
    @{" File handling " LINK "Preferences File Handling Page" }
    @{" Indicators    " LINK "Preferences Indicators Page"    }
    @{" Commodity     " LINK "Preferences Commodity Page"     }

     @{u}Buttons@{uu}

    @{" Save   " LINK "Preferences Save Button"   }
    @{" Use    " LINK "Preferences Use Button"    }
    @{" Test   " LINK "Preferences Test Button"   }
    @{" Cancel " LINK "Preferences Cancel Button" }

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Preferences Save Button"

This button permanently saves your changes to Scatterbrain's configuration.
The changes take effect immediately, and the @{" preferences window " LINK "Preferences Window"} closes.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Preferences Use Button"

This button saves your changes to Scatterbrain's configuration.  The
changes take effect immediately, and the @{" preferences window " LINK "Preferences Window"} closes.
These changes will remain in effect until you reboot your Amiga.

@endnode

------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Preferences Test Button"

This button causes changes you have made to Scatterbrain's configuration
to take effect, without the changes being saved.  These changes will 
remain in effect until you quit Scatterbrain.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Preferences Cancel Button"

This button cancels any changes you may have made to the preferences
gadgets since the last time you saved, used, or loaded preferences.
Also, the @{" preferences window " LINK "Preferences Window"} closes. 

Using this gadget differs from merely clicking the close gadget,
because using the close gadget will not undo any changes you have
made to the preferences gadgets.  Instead, the next time you open
the @{" preferences window " LINK "Preferences Window"}, your changes will still be there, waiting
for you to click @{" Save " LINK "Preferences Save Button"}, @{" Use " LINK "Preferences Use Button"}, or @{" Test " LINK "Preferences Test Button"} so that they may take 
effect.

@endnode
========================================================================
@node "Preferences Input Page"

This page contains only the @{" input screen gadget " LINK "Input Screen Gadget"}.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Input Screen Gadget"

Here you can configure on which screen the @{" input window " LINK "Input Window"} should pop up.

The input window is allowed to appear on a different screen than the
rest of the Scatterbrain windows so that you will be able to input your
ideas quickly, before you forget them.  For this, you may want it to
always appear on the frontmost screen, for example.

There are three choices:

        Scatterbrain    -- Whichever screen you have configured
                           Scatterbrain to use via the MUI Prefs
                           program, will also be used for the
                           @{" Input Window " LINK "Input Window"}.

        Workbench       -- The Input Window will appear on the
                           Workbench screen, regardless of which
                           screen the other windows appear on.

        default public  -- The Input Window will appear on the
                           default public screen, regardless of
                           which screen the other windows appear 
                           on.  If you change the default public
                           screen, and you want to move the Input
                           Window, close it and then press the
                           @{" hotkey " LINK "Hotkey"} to re-open it.

@endnode
========================================================================
@node "Preferences Queue Page"

     @{u}Gadgets@{uu}

    @{" Sort   " LINK "Sort Queue Gadget"      }
    @{" Insert " LINK "Insert Queue Gadget"    }
    @{" Grab   " LINK "Grab From Queue Gadget" }

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Sort Queue Gadget"

If this gadget is checked off, the @{" Queue Listview " LINK "Queue Listview"} will be maintained
in sorted order.  Otherwise, new items will enter the queue listview
according to the setting of the @{" Insert gadget " LINK "Insert Queue Gadget"}.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Insert Queue Gadget"

This cycle gadget specifies where in the @{" Queue Listview " LINK "Queue Listview"} a new item
will be placed.  Items may be placed in the queue listview either by
input from the @{" Input Gadget " LINK "Input Gadget"}, or from a text file via the @{" Import " LINK "PRoject-Import Menu Item"}
menu item on the @{" Project menu " LINK "Project Menu"}.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Grab From Queue Gadget"

This cycle gadget specifies which item from the @{" Queue Listview " LINK "Queue Listview"} will
be added as a step to the active project in the @{" Projects Listview " LINK "Project Listview"}
when the @{" grab button " LINK "Project Grab Button"} is pressed.  

@endnode
========================================================================
@node "Preferences Projects Page"

    @{u}Gadgets on the Symbols Page@{uu}

    @{" Hidden " LINK "Hidden Prefix Gadget" }
    @{" Shown  " LINK "Shown Prefix Gadget"  }
    @{" Indent " LINK "Indent With Gadget"   }

    @{u}Gadgets on the Behaviors Page@{uu}

    @{" Show/Hide set change indicator " LINK "ShowHideMod"                }
    @{" Always use prefix symbols      " LINK "ShowHideChildless"          }
    @{" Find hidden project            " LINK "Find Hidden Project Gadget" }
    @{" Finding project opens window   " LINK "FindActivate"               }

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Hidden Prefix Gadget"

This gadget specifies the text or image that will be displayed next
to a project if its steps and sub-projects are hidden.  To specify
an image instead of plaint text, use a @{" MUI escape sequence " LINK MUIEsc}.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Shown Prefix Gadget"

This gadget specifies the text or image that will be displayed next
to a project if its steps and sub-projects are not hidden.  To specify
an image instead of plaint text, use a @{" MUI escape sequence " LINK MUIEsc}.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Indent With Gadget"

The text (or image) specified by this gadget is used to indent steps
and sub-projects displayed beneath their parent projects in the
@{" Projects Listview " LINK "Project Listview"}.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node ShowHideMod "Show/Hide Change Gadget"

If this gadget is checked, the @{" Change Indicator " LINK "Change Indicator"} will be visible in
the @{" Input Window " LINK "Input Window"}, and will change its appearance based on whether 
there are changes in the database which need to be saved to disk.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node ShowHideChildless "Always Use Prefix Symbols"

If this gadget is checked, either the "Shown" or "Hidden" symbol
will be displayed before every project, even if it has no steps
to hide or show.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Find Hidden Project Gadget"

Double-clicking an entry in the @{" checklist " LINK "Checklist listview"} or the @{" Synonym Listview " LINK "Synonym Listview"}
may cause an entry in the @{" Projects Listview " LINK "Project Listview"} to be highlighted.  This
gadget controls that behavior.

Find    @{b}only visible projects@{ub}   -- will highlight the project
if it is currently shown.

Find @{b}hidden project's ancestors@{ub} -- will highlight the project
if it is currently shown, or the deepest visible ancestor, if it is not.

Find @{b}and reveal hidden projects@{ub} -- will highlight the project
even if it is not visible, by un-hiding whatever projects it has to.
This behavior is always available in the @{" Checklist " LINK "Checklist Window"} and @{" Synonym " LINK "Synonym Window"}
windows by pressing ctrl-f instead of f for the Find button.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node FindActivate "Finding Project Opens Window Gadget"

Double-clicking an entry in the @{" checklist " LINK "Checklist listview"} or the @{" Synonym Listview " LINK "Synonym Listview"}
may cause an entry in the @{" Projects Listview " LINK "Project Listview"} to be highlighted.  If this
gadget is checked, the @{" Projects Window " LINK "Projects Window"} will also open if it wasn't
already, and become the active window.

@endnode
========================================================================
@node "Preferences Project Info Page"

This window contains only the @{" Close Project Info " LINK "Close PInfo Gadget"} gadget.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Close PInfo Gadget" "Auto-close Project Info Gadget"

If this gadget is selected, then clicking the @{" Use " LINK "PInfo Use"} or @{" Cancel " LINK "PInfo Cancel"} buttons
or selecting the @{" Use menu item " LINK "Project Info-Use Menu Item"} or @{" Restore menu item " LINK "Project Info-Restore Menu Item"} from the
@{" Project Info menu " LINK "Project Info Menu"} will cause the @{" Project Info Window " LINK "Project Info Window"} to close after
performing the desired function.  This may be convenient for some, or
annoying for others, so it is left as a configurable option.

@endnode
========================================================================
@node "Preferences Checklist Page"

      @{u}Gadgets@{uu}

    @{" Sort by due date      " LINK "Sort Checklist Gadget"  }
    @{" Show parent's synonym " LINK "Show Synonym Gadget"    }
    @{" Checklist font        " LINK "Checklist Font Gadget"  }
    @{" Checklist image       " LINK "Checklist Image Gadget" }

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Sort Checklist Gadget"

If this gadget is checked, the @{" Checklist Listview " LINK "Checklist Listview"} will be sorted.
Those items which have their due date field filled in will come first,
sorted by that date.  Those items which don't have a specific due date
will follow.  If this gadget is not checked, the checklist will be in
the same order as the items appear in the @{" Projects Listview " LINK "Project Listview"}.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Show Synonym Gadget"

If this gadget is selected, the items in the @{" checklist " LINK "Checklist listview"} will be 
prefixed by the @{" label " LINK Synonym} which refers to their respective "parent"
projects.  You may find this useful to help identify otherwise
cryptic project steps.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Checklist Font Gadget"

Here you may select the font used for the @{" Checklist Listview " LINK "Checklist Listview"}.
A different font is allowed for the checklist in order  to make 
that window stand out from the others.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Checklist Image Gadget"

Here you may select the image used for the checkmarks in the left
column of the @{" Checklist Listview " LINK "Checklist Listview"}.  You may use one of the images
provided with this program, or any other image or text that MUI
allows.

@endnode
========================================================================
@node "Preferences File Handling Page"

      @{u}Gadgets@{uu}

    @{" Autoload     " LINK "Autoload Gadget"                }
    @{" Backup       " LINK "Keep Backup Gadget"             }
    @{" Extension    " LINK "Backup Extension Gadget"        }
    @{" Overwrite    " LINK "Confirm Overwrite Gadget"       }
    @{" Lose Changes " LINK "Confirm Loss of Changes Gadget" }

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Autoload Gadget"

If a filename is entered in this gadget, that file will be loaded
automatically when Scatterbrain is started.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Keep Backup Gadget"

If this gadget is selected, a backup file will be made before an existing
file is overwritten by the @{" Save " LINK "Project-Save Menu Item"}, @{" Save As " LINK "Project-Save As Menu Item"}, or @{" Print To File " LINK "Checklist-Print-To File Menu Sub-item"} menu
items.  The back file will have the same name as the file it is replacing,
except any @{" extension " LINK "extension"} will be replaced by the value specified by the
@{" Backup Extenstion Gadget " LINK "Backup Extension Gadget"}.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Backup Extension Gadget"

This gadget specifies the @{" file extension " LINK "extension"} used if the @{" Keep Backup " LINK "Keep Backup Gadget"}
gadget is selected.  If this gadget is empty, the string "bak" is used
as the extension.  Do not enter a "." before the extension you enter,
because one is supplied when the extension is added to the main
filename.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Confirm Overwrite Gadget"

If this gadget is selected, Scatterbrain will prompt you before @{" Save " LINK "Project-Save Menu Item"},
@{" Save As " LINK "Project-Save As Menu Item"}, or @{" Print To File " LINK "Checklist-Print-To File Menu Sub-item"} overwrites an existing file.  If this
gadget is not selected, existing files will be overwritten quietly.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Confirm Loss of Changes Gadget"

If this gadget is selected, Scatterbrain will prompt you to save your
data before loading, reverting, or quitting, if you have made changes
to the data since the last time it was saved.  If this gadget is not
selected, changes will be lost quietly.

@endnode
========================================================================
@node "Preferences Indicators Page"

      @{u}Gadgets@{uu}

    @{" Show gauges during main I/O   " LINK "Show Gauges Gadget #1"      }
    @{" Show gauges during other work " LINK "Show Gauges Gadget #2"      }
    @{" Indicate if changed           " LINK "Indicate Gadget"            }
    @{" Changed indicator             " LINK "Changed Indicator Gadget"   }
    @{" Unchanged indicator           " LINK "Unchanged Indicator Gadget" }

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Show Gauges Gadget #1"

If this gadget is checked, the @{" Gauge Window " LINK "Gauge Window"} will appear during "load"
and "save" operations.  In addition to showing how close to completion
the "load" or "save" is, this window provides an @{" abort button " LINK "Gauges Abort Button"} for
cancelling a "load" or "save" in progress.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Show Gauges Gadget #2"

If this gadget is checked, the @{" Gauge Window " LINK "Gauge Window"} will appear when you
select an operation from the @{" Checklist Menu " LINK "Checklist Menu"}.  Only the Checklist gauge
will be used to show progress.  Pressing the @{" Abort button " LINK "Gauges Abort Button"} will stop
whatever operation you have selected.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Indicate Gadget"

If this gadget is checked, an @{" indicator gadget " LINK "Change Indicator"} will appear in the
@{" Input Window " LINK "Input Window"}.  This indicator will display one text or image when
there are no changes which need to be saved, and a different one when
there are changes to be saved.  These texts or images may be configured
by the @{" Unchanged indicator " LINK "Unchanged Indicator Gadget"} and @{" Changed indicator " LINK "Changed Indicator Gadget"} gadgets,
respectively.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Changed Indicator Gadget"

This text specifies what should appear in the @{" Indicator Gadget " LINK "Change Indicator"} when
changes have been made to the data which need to be saved.  An image
may be specified by using a @{" MUI escape sequence " LINK MUIEsc}.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Unchanged Indicator Gadget"

This text specifies what should appear in the @{" Indicator Gadget " LINK "Change Indicator"} when
no changes have been made to the data which need to be saved.  An image
may be specified by using a @{" MUI escape sequence " LINK MUIEsc}.  You may wish to
leave this gadget empty, so that the @{" Changed Indicator " LINK "Changed Indicator Gadget"} sequence will
stand out more when it is present.

@endnode
========================================================================
@node "Preferences Commodity Page"

      @{u}Gadgets@{uu}

    @{" Hotkey    " LINK "Hotkey String Gadget" }
    @{" Popup     " LINK "Popup Gadget"         }
    @{" Popup All " LINK "Popup All Gadget"     }
    @{" AppIcon   " LINK "AppIcon Gadget"       }

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Hotkey String Gadget"

This string describes the @{" hotkey " LINK "Hotkey"} used to uniconify Scatterbrain 
and/or activate the @{" Input Gadget " LINK "Input Gadget"}.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Popup Gadget"

If this gadget is checked, the @{" Input Window " LINK "Input Window"} will open when 
Scatterbrain starts.  You may wish to uncheck this gadget if
you place Scatterbrain in your WBStartup drawer.  

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Popup All Gadget"

If this gadget is checked, and the @{" Popup Gadget " LINK "Popup Gadget"} is checked, several
windows will be opened when Scatterbrain is first run, including the
@{" Input Window " LINK "Input Window"}, @{" Queue Window " LINK "Queue Window"}, @{" Projects Window " LINK "Projects Window"}, @{" Synonym Window " LINK "Synonym Window"}
and @{" Checklist Window " LINK "Checklist Window"}.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "AppIcon Gadget"

This gadget allows you to configure which icon will be used when you
iconify Scatterbrain.  The ".info" extension will be added automatically
when Scatterbrain loads the icon, so don't type it in here!

@endnode
========================================================================
@node "About Window"

This window displays the @{" about text " LINK "SB Query About"}, which tells you about which 
version of Scatterbrain you have.  To close the About Window, you can
use the close gadget, click on "Ok", or just press the return key.

@endnode
========================================================================
@node "Gauge Window"

This window displays the progress of the current load or save operation.
There are four gauges, labeled "Queue", "Projects", "Checklist" and
"Synonyms", respectively.  Each displays the progress of loading or
saving the corresponding section of the data file.  Usually, the
"Projects" section takes the longest to load, since it has the most
complex data structure.  The process of loading or saving can be aborted
by clicking on the @{" abort button " LINK "Gauges Abort Button"}.

This window may also be displayed during other potentially time-consuming
operations, such as generating, reconciling, or printinga checklist.

Whether or not the Gauge Window is displayed is controlled by the
two "Show Gauges" gadgets on the on the @{" Indicator Page " LINK "Preferences Indicator Page"} of the 
@{" Preferences Window " LINK "Preferences Window"}.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Gauges Abort Button"

Clicking this button causes the current operation to stop immediately.
If you interrupt a load operation, the partially loaded database will be
cleared from memory.  If you interrupt a save operation, the partial
file will remain on disk -- you should delete it!  In a @{" future version " LINK future},
this may be taken care of automatically.

@endnode
========================================================================
@node Menus

         @{u}Menus@{uu}

    @{" Project      " LINK "Project Menu"     }
    @{" Windows      " LINK "Windows Menu"     }

    @{" Queue        " LINK "Queue Menu"       }
    @{" Projects     " LINK "Projects Menu"    } 
    @{" Project Info " LINK "Project Info Menu"} 
    @{" Checklist    " LINK "Checklist Menu"   } 
    @{" Preferences  " LINK "Preferences Menu" } 
    @{" Pages        " LINK "Pages Menu"       } 

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Project Menu"

     @{u}Menu items@{uu}

    @{" New      " LINK "Project-New Menu Item"      }    Erase all data
    @{" Open     " LINK "Project-Open Menu Item"     }    Open a data file
    @{" Save     " LINK "Project-Save Menu Item"     }    Save the current file 
    @{" Save as  " LINK "Project-Save as Menu Item"  }    Save to a different filename

    @{" Revert   " LINK "Project-Revert Menu Item"   }    Reload data file from disk
    @{" Import   " LINK "Project-Import Menu Item"   }    Import a text file

    @{" About    " LINK "Project-About Menu Item"    }    Display the About Window

    @{" Hide All " LINK "Project-Hide All Menu Item" }    Close all windows
    @{" Iconify  " LINK "Project-Iconify Menu Item"  }    Iconify

    @{" Quit     " LINK "Project-Quit Menu Item"     }    Quit

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Project-New Menu Item"

Erases all current data.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Project-Open Menu Item"

Select a Scatterbrain data file to be loaded.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Project-Save Menu Item"

Save the current data to the current filename.  To change the filename,
select @{" Save as " LINK "Project-Save as Menu Item"} instead.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Project-Save as Menu Item"

Select a file, via a standard file requester, in which to save the
current data.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Project-Revert Menu Item"

Undo any changes since the last load or save by reloading the file from
disk.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Project-Import Menu Item"

Each line of the text file -- which you specify via a standard file
requester -- is treated as if it had been entered via the @{" Input Gadget " LINK "Input Gadget"}.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Project-About Menu Item"

Display the @{" About Window " LINK "About Window"}.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Project-Hide All Menu Item"

Closes all windows.  Press the @{" hotkey " LINK Hotkey} to re-open the @{" input window " LINK "Input Window"}.
Then, you can use the @{" windows menu " LINK "Windows Menu"} to reopen any of the other windows,
if you wish.  

This is very similar to the @{" Iconify " LINK "Project-Iconify Menu Item"} menu item, except for three
differences:

    1. If you are using MUI's public screen manager, the screen 
       will not close when all the windows do.

    2. No icon will appear on the Workbench

    3. When you press the @{" hotkey " LINK "Hotkey"}, only the @{" Input Window " LINK "Input Window"} will
       open.  If you had other windows open when you selected
       "Hide All", they will remain closed.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Project-Iconify Menu Item"

Selecting this menu item is equivalent to click on the MUI iconify
gadget in any of the Scatterbrain windows.  All the windows will be
closed and an icon will appear on the Workbench.  If Scatterbrain was
opened on a MUI public screen, that screen may close.  Double-clicking
on the icon or pressing the @{" hotkey " LINK Hotkey} will cause the screen and windows
to reopen.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Project-Quit Menu Item"

Causes the Scatterbrain application to quit.  If any changes have been
made to the data, and you have not saved, the changes may be lost.

If the @{" Confirm Loss of Changes " LINK "Confirm Loss of Changes Gadget"} gadget is checked off on the 
@{" File Handling Page " LINK "Preferences File Handling Page"} of the @{" Preferences Window " LINK "Preferences Window"}, you will be given
a chance to save your data first.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Windows Menu"

Each menu item opens the corresponding window, or brings it to the front,
if it was already open.

       @{u}Menu items@{uu}

    @{" Input        " LINK "Windows-Input Menu Item"        } 
    @{" Queue        " LINK "Windows-Queue Menu Item"        } 
    @{" Projects     " LINK "Windows-Projects Menu Item"     } 
    @{" Synonyms     " LINK "Windows-Synonyms Menu Item"     } 
    @{" Project Info " LINK "Windows-Project Info Menu Item" } 
    @{" Checklist    " LINK "Windows-Checklist Menu Item"    } 

    @{" Preferences  " LINK "Windows-Preferences Menu Item"  } 

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Windows-Input Menu Item"

Opens the @{" input window " LINK "Input Window"}, if it was closed, and brings it to the front.
Will also activate the @{" input gadget " LINK "Input Gadget"}, if possible.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Windows-Queue Menu Item"

Opens the @{" queue window " LINK "Queue Window"}, if it was closed, and brings it to the front.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Windows-Projects Menu Item"

Opens the @{" projects window " LINK "Projects Window"}, if it was closed, and brings it to the 
front.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Windows-Synonyms Menu Item"

Opens the @{" synonyms window " LINK "Synonyms Window"}, if it was closed, and brings it to the
front.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Windows-Project Info Menu Item"

Opens the @{" project info window " LINK "Project Info Window"}, if it was closed, and brings it to
the front.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Windows-Checklist Menu Item"

Opens the @{" checklist window " LINK "Checklist Window"}, if it was closed, and brings it to the
front.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Windows-Preferences Menu Item"

Opens the @{" preferences window " LINK "Preferences Window"}, if it was closed, and brings it to the
front.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Queue Menu"

   @{u}Menu items@{uu}

    @{" File " LINK "Queue-File Menu Item" } 
    @{" Sort " LINK "Queue-Sort Menu Item" } 

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Queue-File Menu Item"

Selecting this menu item causes Scatterbrain to reattempt to file each
line in the @{" Queue Listview " LINK "Queue Listview"}.

This may be useful if you entered several items using a @{" label " LINK Synonym} which
did not yet exist in the @{" Synonym Listview " LINK "Synonym Listview"}.  After adding it, you can
select this menu item to file those items as steps under the appropriate
project.

This operation may also be useful after selecting @{" Import " LINK "Project-Import Menu Item"} from the
@{" Project menu " LINK "Project Menu"}, if the imported text lines were not properly ordered
for all of them to be filed initially.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Queue-Sort Menu Item"

Sorts the contents of the @{" Queue Listview " LINK "Queue Listview"} in alphabetical order.
Additional input to the queue listview will not be inserted in
sorted order unless the @{" sort gadget " LINK "Sort Queue Gadget"} on the @{" Queue Page " LINK "Preferences Queue Page"} of the
@{" Preferences Window " LINK "Preferences Window"} is selected.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Projects Menu"

   @{u}Menu items@{uu}

    @{" Done      " LINK "Projects-Done Menu Item"      } 
    Postpone >        
        @{" one day   " LINK "-Postpone-one day Menu Sub-item"   } 
        @{" one week  " LINK "-Postpone-one week Menu Sub-item"  } 
        @{" one month " LINK "-Postpone-one month Menu Sub-item" }
        @{" one year  " LINK "-Postpone-one year Menu Sub-item"  }

    @{" Show Info " LINK "Projects-Show Info Menu Item" } 

    @{" Expire    " LINK "Projects-Expire Menu Item"    } 
    @{" Flush     " LINK "Projects-Flush Menu Item"     } 

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Projects-Done Menu Item" 

Puts all the selected projects in the Done state.  This is much quicker
than selecting @{" Show Info " LINK "Projects-Show Info Menu Item"} for each item, changing the state to Done,
and clicking the @{" Use " LINK "PInfo Use"} button in the @{" Project Info Window " LINK "Project Info Window"}.  

If the selected items were represented in the @{" checklist " LINK "Checklist listview"}, they will
be removed from it when their state changes to Done.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "-Postpone-one day Menu Sub-item" 

Causes the @{" display date " LINK "PInfo Display"} of the project(s) selected to be advanced by
one day.  If the display date is not set, it will be set to tomorrow's
date.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "-Postpone-one week Menu Sub-item" 

Causes the @{" display date " LINK "PInfo Display"} of the project(s) selected to be advanced
by one week.  If the display date is not set, it will be set to one
week from today.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "-Postpone-one month Menu Sub-item" 

Causes the @{" display date " LINK "PInfo Display"} of the project(s) selected to be advanced
by one month.  If the display date is not set, it will be set to one
month from today.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "-Postpone-one year Menu Sub-item" 

Causes the @{" display date " LINK "PInfo Display"} of the project(s) selected to be advanced
by one year.  If the display date is not set, it will be set to one
year from today.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Projects-Show Info Menu Item"

Selecting this menu item opens the @{" Project Info Window " LINK "Project Info Window"}, filling in
the gadgets with information from the project under the cursor in the
@{" Projects Listview " LINK "Project Listview"}.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Projects-Expire Menu Item"

Selecting this menu item causes the project database to be searched
for projects or steps which are "Ready" and which have an expiration
date which is in the past.  All projects and steps found are put into
the "Expired" state.  Selecting the @{" Flush item " LINK "Projects-Flush Menu Item"} from the @{" Projects Menu " LINK "Projects Menu"}
will then cause them to be deleted.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Projects-Flush Menu Item"

Selecting this menu item causes the project database to be flushed of
all projects which are either "Done" or "Expired".  The projects and
all their subprojects are deleted, as are any related entries in the
@{" Checklist Listview " LINK "Checklist Listview"} and the @{" Synonym Listview " LINK "Synonym Listview"}.  Note: If a project
is "Done" or "Expired", but it has subprojects which are not, the
subprojects will be deleted anyway.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Project Info Menu"

    @{u}Menu items@{uu}

    Postpone >        
        @{" one day   " LINK "-Postpone-one day Menu Sub-item"   } 
        @{" one week  " LINK "-Postpone-one week Menu Sub-item"  } 
        @{" one month " LINK "-Postpone-one month Menu Sub-item" }
        @{" one year  " LINK "-Postpone-one year Menu Sub-item"  }

    @{" Use     " LINK "Project Info-Use Menu Item"     } 
    @{" Restore " LINK "Project Info-Restore Menu Item" } 

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Project Info-Use Menu Item"

Causes the data in the @{" Project Info Window " LINK "Project Info Window"} to take effect on the
previously selected project.  The project is selected by double-clicking
on its description in the @{" Projects Listview " LINK "Project Listview"}, or by choosing @{" Show Info " LINK "Projects-Show Info Menu Item"} 
from the @{" Projects Menu " LINK "Projects Menu"}.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Project Info-Restore Menu Item"

Causes any changes made in the @{" Project Info Window " LINK "Project Info Window"} to be undone.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Checklist Menu"

       @{u}Menu items@{uu}

    @{" Generate     " LINK "Checklist-Generate Menu Item"  } 
    @{" Reconcile    " LINK "Checklist-Reconcile Menu Item" } 
    Print >
        @{" to file... " LINK "Checklist-Print-To File Menu Sub-item"    } 
        @{" to printer " LINK "Checklist-Print-To Printer Menu Sub-item" } 

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Checklist-Generate Menu Item"

Selecting this menu item causes a new checklist to be generated.  

The procedure is as follows:

From every "do in sequence" project, the first subproject which is not
"Done" or "Expired", is selected for the checklist.  If that project
has subprojects, then this procedure is repeated recursively for the
first of those subprojects.

For now, "do in any order" projects are treated as above.  This should
change in a future version of Scatterbrain.

All the subprojects of a "do all at once" project are selected.  The
procedure is repeated recursively for any of those subprojects which
themselves have subprojects.

If a project is marked as "do just one of", then the project itself
will be selected, instead of any subprojects, if it is selected by
one of the preceding rules.

Finally, if a project is marked as "do not generate", none of its
subprojects will ever be considered for the checklist.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Checklist-Reconcile Menu Item"

Causes the checklist to be reconciled with the @{" Projects Listview " LINK "Project Listview"}.
All items checked off in the @{" Checklist Listview " LINK "Checklist Listview"} are deleted from it,
and the corresponding project is put in the "Done" state.  The "Acted
on" date for that project and all its parents is set to the current
date and time.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Checklist-Print-To File Menu Sub-item"

Write the current checklist to a text file whose name you specify via a
standard file requester.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Checklist-Print-To Printer Menu Sub-item"

Write the current checklist to the PRT: device.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Preferences Menu"

     @{u}Menu items@{uu}

    @{" Open...    " LINK "Preferences-Open Menu Item"       } 
    @{" Last Saved " LINK "Preferences-Last Saved Menu Item" } 
    @{" Restore    " LINK "Preferences-Restore Menu Item"    } 
    @{" Save as... " LINK "Preferences-Save as... Menu Item" } 

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Preferences-Open Menu Item"

Loads the preferences saved in the file which you select via a standard
file requester.  You must click the @{" Save " LINK "Preferences Save Button"}, @{" Use " LINK "Preferences Use Button"}, or @{" Test " LINK "Preferences Test Button"} gadget 
for the values to take effect.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Preferences-Last Saved Menu Item"

Loads the preferences as they were the last time the @{" Save button " LINK "Preferences Save Button"} was
pressed.  You must click the @{" Save " LINK "Preferences Save Button"}, @{" Use " LINK "Preferences Use Button"}, or @{" Test " LINK "Preferences Test Button"} button for them
to take effect.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Preferences-Restore Menu Item"

Loads the preferences as they were the last time either the @{" Use " LINK "Preferences Use Button"}
button or the @{" Save " LINK "Preferences Save Button"} button was pressed.  You must click the @{" Save " LINK "Preferences Save Button"}, 
@{" Use " LINK "Preferences Use Button"}, or @{" Test " LINK "Preferences Test Button"} button for the restored preferences to take effect.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Preferences-Save as... Menu Item"

Saves the current preferences settings to a file.  The name of this file
is selected via a standard file requester.  This does @{b}not@{ub} cause the
preferences to take effect.

@endnode
------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Pages Menu"

     @{u}Menu items@{uu}

    @{" Input         " LINK "Pages-Input Menu Item"        } 
    @{" Queue         " LINK "Pages-Queue Menu Item"        } 
    Projects >
        @{" Symbols   " LINK "Pages-Projects-Symbols Menu Sub-item"   } 
        @{" Behaviors " LINK "Pages-Projects-Behaviors Menu Sub-item" }
    @{" Project Info  " LINK "Pages-Project Info Menu Item" } 
    @{" Checklist     " LINK "Pages-Checklist Menu Item"    } 
    @{" File Handling " LINK "Pages-File Handling Menu Item"} 
    @{" Indicators    " LINK "Pages-Indicators Menu Item"   } 
    @{" Commodity     " LINK "Pages-Commodity Menu Item"    } 

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Pages-Input Menu Item"

Selecting this menu item causes the @{" Input Page " LINK "Preferences Input Page"} to be displayed in the
@{" Preferences Window " LINK "Preferences Window"}.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Pages-Queue Menu Item"

Selecting this menu item causes the @{" Queue Page " LINK "Preferences Queue Page"} to be displayed in the
@{" Preferences Window " LINK "Preferences Window"}.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Pages-Projects-Symbols Menu Sub-item"

Selecting this menu item causes the symbols subpage to be displayed on
the @{" Projects Page " LINK "Preferences Projects Page"} of the @{" Preferences Window " LINK "Preferences Window"}.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Pages-Projects-Behaviors Menu Sub-item"

Selecting this menu item causes the behaviors subpage to be displayed on
the @{" Projects Page " LINK "Preferences Projects Page"} of the @{" Preferences Window " LINK "Preferences Window"}.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Pages-Project Info Menu Item"

Selecting this menu item causes the @{" Project Info Page " LINK "Preferences Project Info Page"} to be displayed
in the @{" Preferences Window " LINK "Preferences Window"}.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Pages-Checklist Menu Item"

Selecting this menu item causes the @{" checklist page " LINK "Preferences Checklist Page"} to be displayed in
the @{" Preferences Window " LINK "Preferences Window"}.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Pages-File Handling Menu Item"

Selecting this menu item causes the @{" file handling page " LINK "Preferences File Handling Page"} to be displayed
in the @{" Preferences Window " LINK "Preferences Window"}.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Pages-Indicators Menu Item"

Selecting this menu item causes the @{" Indicators Page " LINK "Preferences Indicators Page"} to be displayed in
the @{" Preferences Window " LINK "Preferences Window"}.

@endnode
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
@node "Pages-Commodity Menu Item"

Selecting this menu item causes the @{" Commodity Page " LINK "Preferences Commodity Page"} to be displayed
in the @{" Preferences Window " LINK "Preferences Window"}.

@endnode
